<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-69-0986 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author discusses how the strategic defense initiative can contributeto curbing strategic arms competition by devaluing nuclear missiles.He says the Americans though in the 1970s that if the U.S. curbed itsnuclear buildup so would the Soviets. This was wrong. Improvements andadditions to the Soviet missile force continued. He says the U.S. musttry to get the Soviet Union to work with the U.S. to make the threatof nuclear destruction impotent.</TEXT></DOC>